  "text": "Extensive psychophysical studies have established that adult spatial vision is fundamentally limited by crowding-the reduced ability to identify an object in the periphery when it is surrounded by other objects [CITATION_1] . This limit extends beyond that of visual acuity, because even though the object is still visible, it is not readily identifiable.",
